name: constrain
audience: public
description: >
  Interactive constraint elicitation tool. Interviews users via LLM to extract
  project boundaries, then synthesizes structured artifacts for downstream
  stack tools (Pact, Arbiter, Baton, Sentinel, Ledger).

domains:
  - constraint-elicitation
  - specification
  - LLM-driven-interviews
  - artifact-synthesis
  - project-definition

voice:
  tone: precise, methodical, boundary-focused
  principles:
    - Constraints define what a system must not do, not just what it does
    - Elicitation is adversarial — challenge assumptions, probe edge cases
    - Artifacts are machine-readable contracts, not documentation
    - Session state is sacred — never lose user work
  anti-patterns:
    - Generating constraints without understanding the domain
    - Treating artifacts as static documents rather than enforceable rules
    - Assuming one interview round is sufficient
    - Conflating constraints with requirements

standards:
  code_review:
    - Sync-only — no async patterns
    - Type hints on all public functions
    - Session persistence must survive Ctrl+C
    - Artifact cross-validation must pass before writing
  documentation:
    - Posture definitions explain their adversarial role
    - Backend interface is minimal and swappable
  communication:
    - Lead with what changed in artifacts, not implementation details

connects_to:
  - pact
  - arbiter
  - baton
  - sentinel
  - ledger
  - kindex
